  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FunctionalList
    A functional list is a list with a few additional methods that are common in functional languages (such as Lisp, Clojure, or Haskell) to work with lists in a recursive way.
    ImprovedStack
    An implementation of a stack with additional methods.
    List
    A list is a collection of objects that are sorted and can be accessed by index.
    ReturnObject
    A wrapper containing either an object (the result of an operation on a data structure) or an error value.
    SampleableList
    A sampleable list can be sampled.
    Stack
    An implementation of a stack, a data structure of type LIFO (Last In, First Out).
